===Biographical===
{{Refbegin}}
* [[Conrad Black|Black, Conrad]]. ''Franklin Delano Roosevelt: Champion of Freedom'', 2003, ISBN 978-1-58648-282-4 : interpretive detailed biography
* [[H. W. Brands|Brands, H.W.]] ''Traitor to His Class: The Privileged Life and Radical Presidency of Franklin Delano Roosevelt'' (2009), ISBN 978-0-385-51958-8 :despite the title, a highly favorable biography by scholar
* {{Cite book|ref=Burns |last= Burns |first=James MacGregor |title= 'Roosevelt' (vol. 1)|year= 1956 |publisher=Easton Press |isbn=978-0-15-678870-0}}
* {{Cite book|ref=Burns2 |last= Burns |first=James MacGregor |title= 'Roosevelt: the soldier of freedom' (vol. 2)|year= 1970 |publisher=Harcourt Brace Jovanovich. |isbn=978-0-15-678870-0}} [http://hdl.handle.net/2027/heb.00626 online edition]
* {{cite book |title=Eleanor Roosevelt, Volume 1 |last=Cook |first=Blanche Wiesen |authorlink=Blanche Wiesen Cook |year=1992 |publisher=Penguin |isbn=0140094601 |ref=harv}}
* [[Frank Freidel|Freidel, Frank]]. ''Franklin D. Roosevelt: A Rendezvous with Destiny'' (1990), ISBN 978-0-316-29260-3 : One-volume scholarly biography; covers entire life
* Freidel, Frank. ''Franklin D. Roosevelt'' (4 vol 1952<U+2013>73), {{OCLC|459748221}} : the most detailed scholarly biography; ends in 1934.
* [[Kenneth S. Davis|Davis, Kenneth S.]] ''FDR: The Beckoning of Destiny, 1882<U+2013>1928'' (1972), ISBN 978-0-399-10998-0 : popular biography
* [[Doris Kearns Goodwin|Goodwin, Doris Kearns]]. ''No Ordinary Time: Franklin and Eleanor Roosevelt: The Home Front in World War II'' (1995), ISBN 978-0-684-80448-4 : popular joint biography
* {{Cite book|ref=Hawley |last=Hawley |first=Ellis |title=The New Deal and the Problem of Monopoly |publisher=Fordham University Press |year=1995 |isbn=0-8232-1609-8}}
* [[Roy Jenkins|Jenkins, Roy]]. ''Franklin Delano Roosevelt'' (2003), ISBN 978-0-8050-6959-4 : short bio from British perspective
* [[Joseph P. Lash|Lash, Joseph P.]] ''Eleanor and Franklin: The Story of Their Relationship Based on Eleanor Roosevelt's Private Papers'' (1971), ISBN 978-0-393-07459-8 : history of a marriage.
* [[Ted Morgan (writer)|Morgan, Ted]], ''FDR: A biography'', (1985), ISBN 978-0-671-45495-1: popular biography
* Pederson, William D. ''A Companion to Franklin D. Roosevelt'' (Blackwell Companions to American History) (2011); 35 essays by scholars
*{{cite book |last=Rowley |first=Hazel |year=2010|title=Franklin and Eleanor: An Extraordinary Marriage |publisher=Farrar, Straus and Giroux |isbn=978-0-374-15857-6 |ref=harv}}
* {{Cite book|ref=Siracusa |last=Siracusa |first=Joseph M. |coauthors=Coleman, David G. |title=Depression to Cold War: a history of America from Herbert Hoover to Ronald Reagan |publisher=Greenwood Publishing |year=2002 |isbn= 978-0-275-97555-5}}
* {{Cite book|ref=Smith |last=Smith |first=Jean Edward|authorlink=Jean Edward Smith|publisher=Random House|location=New York|title=FDR |year=2007 |isbn=978-1-4000-6121-1 |ref=harv}}
* {{Cite book|ref=Tully |last=Tully |first=Grace |title= Franklin Delano Roosevelt, My Boss |publisher=Kessinger Publishing |year= 2005 |isbn=978-1-4179-8926-3}}
* [[Geoffrey Ward|Ward, Geoffrey C.]] ''Before The Trumpet: Young Franklin Roosevelt, 1882<U+2013>1905'' (1985), ISBN 978-0-06-015451-6; ''A First-Class Temperament: The Emergence of Franklin Roosevelt'', (1992), ISBN 978-0-06-016066-1 : covers 1905<U+2013>1932; popular biography
* {{Cite book|ref=Winkler |last=Winkler |first=Allan M. |title=Franklin D. Roosevelt and the Making of Modern America |publisher=Longman Publishing |year=2006 |isbn=0-321-41285-0}}
{{Refend}}

===Scholarly secondary sources===
{{Refbegin}}
* {{Cite book |ref=Adamthwaite |last=Adamthwaite |first=Anthony |title=France and the Coming of the Second World War 1936<U+2013>1939 |publisher=Frank Cass |year=1977}}
